Fitts's Law Compliance: Controls remain accessible (left edge target) while content maximizes viewport.

Advanced Patterns for Production Apps

python
# 1. Conditional Sidebar (Dynamic Controls)
if st.sidebar.checkbox("Advanced Filters"):
    with st.sidebar.expander("🎚️ Fine-tuning"):
        st.slider("Confidence", 0.0, 1.0, 0.5)

# 2. Navigation Sidebar  
page = st.sidebar.selectbox("Navigation", 
                           ["Dashboard", "Analysis", "Settings"])

# 3. Progress Indicators
with st.sidebar:
    progress = st.progress(0)
    status = st.empty()

# 4. Theming
st.sidebar.markdown("### 💾 Export")
if st.sidebar.button("📥 Download CSV"):
    st.download_button(...)

Performance & Scalability Considerations

Render Priority: Sidebar → Main (parallel DOM updates)
Memory: Widgets cached identically to main area
Re-run Impact: Sidebar state preserved across interactions
Mobile: Auto-collapses (<768px), hamburger menu

Recommendation: Always default to sidebar for controls in multi-section dashboards. Reserve main area for data visualizations and KPIs exclusively.

